  "title": "Senior Attractions Hosts (Mount Faber)",
  "description": "<p><strong>2.1 Duties of Senior Attractions Hosts</strong></p><p>i. Open and close attractions.</p><p>ii. Perform duties at assigned deployments within the attractions.</p><p>iii. Conduct daily checks to ensure the attraction is maintained and</p><p>operating in its best working condition at all times.</p><p>iv. Report any defects to the respective Attraction In-Charge and</p><p>relevant departments.</p><p>v. Lead the team in performing housekeeping schedules and assigned</p><p>duties.</p><p>vi. Ensure general cleanliness of front-of-house and back-of-house areas</p><p>in attraction.</p><p>vii. Welcome and provide excellent guest service to all guests</p><p>viii. Perform the role of usher or crowd controller at attractions.</p><p>ix. Actively participate in the implementation of activities organized at</p><p>attractions.</p><p>x. Monitor stock level of consumables (e.g. brochures, first aid supplies,</p><p>torch lights, batteries, etc.) and initiate replenishment as required.</p><p>xi. Ensure operational procedures are consistently adhered to.</p><p>xii. Ensure the safety of guests at all times.</p><p>xiii. Manage guests during attraction downtime or in emergency</p><p>situations.</p><p>xiv. Work cohesively with fellow Attractions Host to deliver operational</p><p>and service excellence.</p><p>xv. Undertake the role of Attraction In-Charge (IC) when necessary.</p><p>xvi. Perform any other duties as assigned by MFLG.</p>",
